---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
	title="Privacy Policy | Data Protection & AdSense Compliance"
	description="Our commitment to your privacy. Learn how we handle local data and comply with Google AdSense and Analytics policies."
>
	<div class="privacy-container">
		<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
		<p class="last-updated">Last updated: January 28, 2026</p>

		<section>
			<h2>1. Introduction</h2>
			<p>
				This policy describes how the "Unix Timestamp Converter" website handles user data. Your privacy is important to us, and we are committed to being transparent about how our tools work.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>2. Data Collection</h2>
			<p>
				This website <strong>does not collect personally identifiable information</strong> directly through forms or registrations. We do not ask for your name, email, or address.
			</p>
			<p>
				We use your browser's <strong>LocalStorage</strong> exclusively for functional purposes, specifically to store your local preferences (such as selected timezone, world clock settings, or "Live" mode), so they remain saved for your next visit. This data is stored locally on your device and is not sent to our servers.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
			<p>
				To support the maintenance of this free tool and analyze traffic, we use the following third-party services:
			</p>
			
			<h3>Google AdSense</h3>
			<p>
				We use Google AdSense to serve advertisements. Google uses cookies to serve ads based on your previous visits to this or other websites. The use of advertising cookies enables Google and its partners to serve ads to you based on your navigation. You can opt-out of personalized advertising by visiting <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ad Settings</a>.
			</p>

			<h3>Google Analytics</h3>
			<p>
				We use Google Analytics to understand how visitors interact with the site (e.g., most visited pages, session duration). This information is collected in an aggregate and anonymous form. Google Analytics uses cookies to generate statistical data.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>4. Consent Management</h2>
			<p>
				Upon your first visit, you may be presented with a banner for cookie consent. You can choose to accept or reject the use of cookies for advertising and analytical purposes. Your choice will be stored locally in your browser.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>5. User Rights</h2>
			<p>
				Since we do not store personal data on our servers, we do not have a database to consult for access or deletion requests. However, you can at any time clear your browser's cache and site data (localStorage and cookies) directly from your browser settings to remove all local traces of your navigation.
			</p>
		</section>

		<div class="back-link">
			<a href="/">&larr; Back to Home</a>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	.privacy-container {
		max-width: 850px;
		margin: 2rem auto;
		background: var(--card-bg);
		backdrop-filter: blur(20px);
		padding: 4rem;
		border-radius: 24px;
		border: 1px solid var(--card-border);
		line-height: 1.8;
	}

	h1 {
		font-size: 3rem;
		font-weight: 800;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		background: linear-gradient(45deg, rgb(var(--accent)), rgb(var(--accent-light)));
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
	}

	.last-updated {
		color: #8b949e;
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		margin-bottom: 4rem;
	}

	h2 {
		color: #fff;
		margin-top: 3rem;
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--card-border);
		padding-bottom: 0.75rem;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	h3 {
		color: #fff;
		margin-top: 2rem;
		font-size: 1.2rem;
		opacity: 0.9;
	}

	p {
		color: #8b949e;
		margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
	}

	strong {
		color: #fff;
	}

	a {
		color: rgb(var(--accent-light));
		text-decoration: none;
		border-bottom: 1px dashed rgba(var(--accent-light), 0.3);
		transition: all 0.2s;
	}

	a:hover {
		color: #fff;
		border-bottom-color: #fff;
	}

	.back-link {
		margin-top: 4rem;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--card-border);
		padding-top: 2rem;
	}

	.back-link a {
		border: none;
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.privacy-container {
			padding: 2rem;
		}
		h1 {
			font-size: 2.2rem;
		}
	}
</style>
